article.headline: Quinnipiac 71, Lehigh 55
article.story: HAMDEN, Conn. (AP) -- DeMario Anderson scored 10 of his 14 points in the final 11 minutes as Quinnipiac pulled away for a 71-55 victory over Lehigh Wednesday. The junior forward hit a pull-up jumper to give the Bobcats a 49-44 lead with 10:40 remaining. His score off an alley-oop from Casey Cosgrove with 57.4 seconds left boosted the lead to 62-53 and helped seal the win. Chris Weyhe led the Bobcats (2-1) with 15 points, while Adam Gonzalez came off the bench to score 11 points and grab seven rebounds. Quinnipiac shot 54.5 percent from the field and forced 14 Lehigh turnovers in the second half to break away from a 32-30 halftime lead. Jose Olivero led all scorers with 17 points while Kyle Neptune added 14 for Lehigh (2-4).
